q 0.7 G 1 w 40 597 m 392 597 l S Q
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 40 572 Td (Gestational diabetes \(GDM\) is high blood sugar that) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 11 Tf 40 555 Td (develops during pregnancy. It affects 2-10% of pregnancies.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 40 525 Td (Key Facts:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 503 Td (- Usually develops around weeks 24-28) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 485 Td (- Usually goes away after delivery) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 467 Td (- Can be managed with diet, exercise, and sometimes insulin) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 449 Td (- Monitoring blood sugar is essential) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 431 Td (- You did NOT cause this - hormones from the placenta block insulin) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 40 400 Td (Why Tracking Matters:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 378 Td (- Helps you see patterns in your blood sugar) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 360 Td (- Identifies foods that spike your levels) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 342 Td (- Provides data for your care team) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 324 Td (- Gives you a sense of control) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 50 306 Td (- Helps ensure healthy outcomes for you and baby) Tj ET
